WEBVTT

00:11.680 --> 00:14.040
[sighs] This is a great idea.

00:14.120 --> 00:15.840
It's been ages
since we got drunk before lunch.

00:15.920 --> 00:18.400
- How about The Bull?
- Uh, no, somewhere further away.

00:19.360 --> 00:21.640
- [Luke] What's on the agenda?
- I just need a drink first.

00:21.720 --> 00:24.560
- Did Abigail get back to you?
- No, nothing. This is really weird.

00:27.160 --> 00:28.920
[line ringing]

00:31.120 --> 00:34.080
I think maybe she slipped out
during Angus' big announcement.

00:34.160 --> 00:35.640
Without telling me?

00:37.640 --> 00:39.920
Uh, she's not picking up.
I'm starting to...

00:40.000 --> 00:41.720
[line continues ringing]

00:42.640 --> 00:44.360
Uh, guys, can we just go via her flat?

00:44.440 --> 00:46.520
- It's a ten-minute detour.
- [Luke] Is everything all right?

00:46.600 --> 00:48.880
I don't know.
Last I knew, everything was fine.

00:48.960 --> 00:50.720
Did you guys...
Did you see anything?

00:50.800 --> 00:52.320
- Well...
- What kind of a well was that?

00:52.400 --> 00:54.480
- I don't really know what I saw.
- What did you see?

00:54.560 --> 00:56.960
Well, it was a...
It was a look.

00:57.040 --> 00:58.400
[stutters] A notable look?

00:58.480 --> 01:01.120
Obviously a notable look, Dylan,
or I wouldn't have noticed it.

01:01.200 --> 01:03.640
But not so notable that
I would have brought it up before now.

01:03.720 --> 01:06.200
I would say it was
at the low end of notable.

01:06.280 --> 01:07.600
What did you see?

01:08.400 --> 01:10.560
Well, I arrived at the party...

01:10.640 --> 01:14.880
and I was... I was feeling good,
you know, it was late in the day...

01:15.800 --> 01:18.480
There was a nice vibe to the place.
Lots of familiar faces.

01:18.560 --> 01:20.800
And for a party celebrating a divorce,

01:20.880 --> 01:23.600
I gotta tell you,
I thought it had an upbeat atmosphere.

01:23.680 --> 01:26.080
Some pretty girls, good drinks.

01:26.160 --> 01:28.800
I knew I looked good in my top.

01:29.720 --> 01:30.920
You know, it just... it just...

01:31.000 --> 01:33.280
It felt really right around my shoulders.

01:34.000 --> 01:37.000
You know how that feels?
When a top just sort of holds you?

01:37.080 --> 01:39.480
Okay, I really don't need to know
how snug your shirt was.

01:39.560 --> 01:41.800
Will you please
just get on with the story? Please.

01:41.880 --> 01:44.320
- Oh! There he is.
- Oh.

01:44.400 --> 01:46.080
Angus. Man of the hour.
All right.

01:46.160 --> 01:48.840
Here is the official proof
that I destroyed my marriage.

01:48.920 --> 01:50.040
On account of my infidelity.

01:50.120 --> 01:52.200
Congratulations.
I think you'll be very happy, mate.

01:52.280 --> 01:55.040
- What, you don't think I'm damaged goods?
- Oh, no, you are. We all are.

01:55.120 --> 01:56.360
I wonder if I look back on today,

01:56.440 --> 01:59.320
if it's the moment that my life
got better or much worse.

01:59.400 --> 02:02.440
I wish I knew which way it was gonna go
and then I'd know how to feel about it.

02:02.520 --> 02:04.440
Me and Evie got this for you.

02:04.520 --> 02:06.040
- Oh.
- [Evie] Don't smoke it all at once.

02:06.120 --> 02:07.480
It's a party. Maybe I'll meet someone.

02:07.560 --> 02:08.560
- [yelling]
- Oh!

02:08.639 --> 02:09.840
[both yelling]

02:10.520 --> 02:11.880
[both laughing]

02:11.960 --> 02:13.960
- First ever divorce party.
- Oh, yeah, mine too.

02:14.040 --> 02:15.040
Oh, yes.

02:15.120 --> 02:16.520
Huh.

02:16.600 --> 02:18.880
You certainly seem to be
the center of attention.

02:18.960 --> 02:20.080
- How long...
- [door opens]

02:21.760 --> 02:23.160
Did you invite Jane?

02:23.240 --> 02:24.800
- Yeah.
- Dude, why?

02:24.880 --> 02:26.800
It's Jane. Everyone loves Jane.

02:26.880 --> 02:29.240
And she was on the groom's side
of the aisle at the wedding.

02:29.320 --> 02:30.360
The wedding where she dumped Dylan?

02:30.440 --> 02:33.560
Yeah. Ah, but if she hadn't done that,
Dylan wouldn't have met Abigail,

02:33.640 --> 02:35.600
and Abigail makes Dylan happy.

02:35.680 --> 02:38.480
- Have you met Abigail yet?
- No.

02:38.560 --> 02:40.080
You know, she's coming tonight.

02:41.520 --> 02:45.240
Oh, well, um, I'm...
looking forward to meeting her.

02:52.960 --> 02:54.240
- Angus...
- Mmm.

02:54.320 --> 02:56.160
who's the girl in the pink dress?

02:57.520 --> 02:59.080
Oh, that's Nicole.
I work with her.

03:02.320 --> 03:03.440
Uh-huh.

03:04.360 --> 03:07.720
[Dylan] Is this gonna end up as a story
about how you slept with Nicole?

03:07.800 --> 03:08.960
[Luke] No, au contraire,

03:09.040 --> 03:11.320
I spent most of the evening
trying not to sleep with her.

03:11.400 --> 03:13.920
I'm trying to ignore my instincts.
It's, uh, my new thing.

03:14.000 --> 03:16.760
Can you just get to the bit where you saw
Abigail's notable look thing?

03:16.840 --> 03:18.240
Yeah, okay, fine.

03:18.320 --> 03:21.000
Basically it was...
it was a look with a kind of...

03:21.080 --> 03:23.560
searching sadness and regret.

03:23.640 --> 03:26.920
We'd just got back from...
Well, never mind that. Anyway...

03:27.000 --> 03:29.120
the actual look was much later on.

